Package: axR
Title: Serial Communication and Data Retrieval for Axivity Devices
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Lucas", "França",
           email = "lucas.franca@northumbria.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0853-1319")))
Description: Serial communication and data retrieval for Axivity AX3/AX6
    accelerometer devices: device discovery, status, settings, data
    download, and reading recorded '.cwa'/AX6 binary files. Wraps the
    Open Movement Project's 'OMAPI' C library (vendored in src/omapi,
    BSD 2-clause, Newcastle University; see src/omapi/LICENSE.TXT),
    rather than reimplementing the serial protocol or binary file format
    directly. Part of the Circadia Lab R ecosystem.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 1.0.0)
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
SystemRequirements: On Linux, libudev (e.g. 'libudev-dev' on
    Debian/Ubuntu) is required for device discovery. macOS and Windows
    use OS frameworks/APIs with no separate install step.
Suggests:
    covr,
    pkgdown,
